!iflang [english]

!begin_node Extended file-selectors

The following functions were introduced with MagiC 4, and permit
management of the file-selector:

!begin_xlist [x fslx_getnxtfile] !compressed
!item [(!bullet) fslx_close]
Closes the file-selector and releases memory
!item [(!bullet) fslx_do]
Faster call-up of the file-selector
!item [(!bullet) fslx_evnt]
Releases file-selector for use
!item [(!bullet) fslx_getnxtfile]
Obtains all further selected entries
!item [(!bullet) fslx_open]
Initializes and opens file-selector
!item [(!bullet) fslx_set_flags]
Sets certain flags for the whole system
!end_xlist

(!B)Note:(!b) The existence of these functions can be checked with a call of
(!link [appl_getinfo][%apgi_7]) (opcode 7).

The main advantage of using these routines lies in the ability of the
functions specified here to work also with alternative file-systems
(catchword: long filenames).

See also: (!nl)
File-selector as a dialog ~ File-selector in a window ~
(!link [Operation of file-selectors][Operation of file-selectors from MagiC 4 onwards])


!else

